<item>
            <title>[SPARK-40622] Result of a single task in collect() must fit in 2GB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-40622</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when collecting results, data from single partition/task is serialized through byte array or ByteBuffer(which is backed by byte array as well), therefore it&apos;s subject to java array max size limit(in terms of byte array, it&apos;s 2GB).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Construct a single partition larger than 2GB and collect it can easily reproduce the issue&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// create data of size ~3GB in single partition, which exceeds the &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;byte&lt;/span&gt; array limit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// random gen to make sure it&apos;s poorly compressed
&lt;/span&gt;val df = spark.range(0, 3000, 1, 1).selectExpr(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, s&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;genData(id, 1000000) as data&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)

withSQLConf(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;spark.databricks.driver.localMaxResultSize&quot;&lt;/span&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;4g&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) {
  withSQLConf(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;spark.sql.useChunkedBuffer&quot;&lt;/span&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;) {
    df.queryExecution.executedPlan.executeCollect()
  }
} &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;will get a OOM error from &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-jdk11/blob/master/src/java.base/share/classes/java/io/ByteArrayOutputStream.java#L125&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/AdoptOpenJDK/openjdk-jdk11/blob/master/src/java.base/share/classes/java/io/ByteArrayOutputStream.java#L125&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider using ChunkedByteBuffer to replace byte array in order to bypassing this limit&lt;/p&gt;</description>
